Then Athtar the Brilliant went up into the uttermost parts of Saphon;
he sat on the throne of Valiant Baal.
But his feet did not reach the footstool

When the mighty one attacks your gate
a vow, Ba’al, we will fulfill;
a firstborn, Ba’al, we will consecrate;
a flesh sacrifice, Ba’al, we will fulfill.

His skin with a stone he scored,
his side-locks with a razor;
he gashed cheeks and chin.

The grain is all spent from its storage;
The wine is all spent from its skins;
The oil is all spent from its casks.
